.\" metalperftrace.1
.Dd May 7, 2026
.Dt METALPERFTRACE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm metalperftrace
.Nd collect and inspect Metal GPU performance data
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar subcommand
.Op options
.Pp
.Nm
.Cm collect
.Op Fl \-last Ar duration | Fl \-start Ar date Fl \-end Ar date
.Op Fl \-prefix Ar prefix
.Op Fl \-json
.Ar output_dir
.Pp
.Nm
.Cm overview
.Op Fl \-json
.Op Fl \-json-include-timeline
.Op Fl \-include-state-transitions
.Op Fl \-predicate Ar expr
.Op Fl \-aggregate
.Op Fl \-start Ar offset
.Op Fl \-end Ar offset
.Op Fl \-domain Ar domain
.Op Fl \-state-label Ar label
.Ar trace_file
.Pp
.Nm
.Cm listen
.Op Fl \-json
.Op Fl \-interval Ar sec
.Op Fl \-output Ar file
.Op Fl \-process Ar name
.Op Fl \-pid Ar pid
.Op Fl \-predicate Ar expr
.Pp
.Nm
.Cm setup
.Fl \-enable Ar feature |
.Fl \-disable Ar feature
.Op Fl \-pid Ar pid
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
collects and inspects always-on recorded Metal graphics performance data.
The system continuously records frame timing and related statistics for all Metal layers.
This tool retrieves that data and either stores it into a trace file that can be opened by
tools such as Instruments, or streams it live as human-readable text or JSON.
.Pp
The following subcommands are available:
.Bl -tag -width "overview"
.It Cm collect
Retrieve always-on recorded Metal performance metrics for a given time range and write them as
.Pa .atrc
files into
.Ar output_dir
(created if it does not exist).
Re-running the same command with the same directory skips files that
were already collected.
.It Cm overview
Print a performance summary from a previously collected
.Pa .atrc
trace file.
By default, prints an aggregation over the entire trace duration.
.It Cm listen
Stream live Metal performance statistics as data arrives from the
system, refreshing on a configurable interval.
.It Cm setup
Dynamically enable or disable a Metal performance trace feature in a running Metal process.
.El
.Sh SUBCOMMAND: COLLECT
.Ss Synopsis
.Nm
.Cm collect
.Op Fl \-last Ar duration | Fl \-start Ar date Fl \-end Ar date
.Op Fl \-prefix Ar prefix
.Op Fl \-json
.Ar output_dir
.Ss Options
.Bl -tag -width "-start date"
.It Fl \-last Ar duration
Collect trace data from the last
.Ar duration .
The suffix determines the unit:
.Sq s
(seconds, default),
.Sq m
(minutes),
.Sq h
(hours),
.Sq d
(days).
A bare number without a suffix is treated as seconds.
Examples:
.Li 30s ,
.Li 5m ,
.Li 2h ,
.Li 1d .
Mutually exclusive with
.Fl \-start .
.It Fl \-start Ar date
Start of the collection window (absolute date).
Accepted formats:
.Li yyyy-MM-dd ,
.Li yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss ,
.Li yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ ,
.Li @unix_timestamp .
Dates in the future are not allowed.
.It Fl \-end Ar date
End of the collection window.
Same format as
.Fl \-start .
Defaults to the current time when omitted.
.It Fl \-prefix Ar prefix
File name prefix for the collected trace files.
Defaults to
.Li MetalPerfTrace .
.It Fl \-json
Output collected file paths as a JSON dictionary with a
.Li traces
key.
Enabled by default when stdout is not a terminal.
.El
.Sh SUBCOMMAND: OVERVIEW
.Ss Synopsis
.Nm
.Cm overview
.Op Fl \-json
.Op Fl \-json-include-timeline
.Op Fl \-include-state-transitions
.Op Fl \-predicate Ar expr
.Op Fl \-aggregate
.Op Fl \-start Ar offset
.Op Fl \-end Ar offset
.Op Fl \-domain Ar domain
.Op Fl \-state-label Ar label
.Ar trace_file
.Ss Description
Print per-process, per-layer performance metrics from a collected trace.
By default, prints an aggregation over the entire trace duration with
full detail for all metric sections.
.Ss Options
.Bl -tag -width "-include-state-transitions"
.It Fl \-json
Emit output as a JSON object instead of human-readable text.
Contains aggregated summary statistics for each layer session.
.It Fl \-json-include-timeline
Include the full per-frame timeline data in JSON output.
Implies
.Fl \-json .
.It Fl \-include-state-transitions
Show detailed StateReporter state transition history, including
labels, time ranges, and stable state values for each domain.
.It Fl \-predicate Ar expr
An NSPredicate expression used to filter the layers shown.
The expression is evaluated against a dictionary with keys:
.Li processName
(string),
.Li pid
(integer),
.Li layerName
(string).
.It Fl \-aggregate
Enable aggregation mode.
Groups metrics by state transitions.
Without additional options, aggregates over all
.Li {domain, label, stableState}
keys across all domains.
.It Fl \-start Ar offset
Start offset from trace start (used with
.Fl \-aggregate ) .
Duration format, e.g.\&
.Li 5s ,
.Li 2m ,
.Li 1h .
.It Fl \-end Ar offset
End offset from trace start (used with
.Fl \-aggregate ) .
Defaults to trace end when omitted.
.It Fl \-domain Ar domain
Restrict aggregation to a single state domain (used with
.Fl \-aggregate ) .
.It Fl \-state-label Ar label
With
.Fl \-domain ,
group by
.Li {domain, label}
only, ignoring stableState differences.
Requires
.Fl \-domain .
.El
.Sh SUBCOMMAND: LISTEN
.Ss Synopsis
.Nm
.Cm listen
.Op Fl \-json
.Op Fl \-interval Ar sec
.Op Fl \-output Ar file
.Op Fl \-process Ar name
.Op Fl \-pid Ar pid
.Op Fl \-predicate Ar expr
.Ss Description
Stream live Metal performance statistics as data arrives from the system.
Always prints full detail for all metric sections.
.Ss Options
.Bl -tag -width "-process name"
.It Fl \-json
Emit each update as a compact JSON object on a single line (NDJSON).
When the session ends (via SIGINT, SIGTERM, or SIGHUP), the output file,
if any, is rewritten as a single pretty-printed JSON array.
.It Fl \-interval Ar sec , Fl i Ar sec
Update interval in seconds.
Minimum:
.Li 1.0 .
Default:
.Li 1.0 .
.It Fl \-output Ar file , Fl o Ar file
Tee all output to
.Ar file
in addition to the terminal.
The file must not already exist.
.It Fl \-process Ar name , Fl p Ar name
Restrict output to the named process.
May be repeated.
.It Fl \-pid Ar pid
Restrict output to the given process ID.
May be repeated.
.It Fl \-predicate Ar expr
Same as for the
.Cm overview
subcommand.
.El
.Sh SUBCOMMAND: SETUP
.Ss Synopsis
.Nm
.Cm setup
.Fl \-enable Ar feature |
.Fl \-disable Ar feature
.Op Fl \-pid Ar pid
.Ss Description
Enable or disable a Metal performance trace feature in one or more running Metal processes.
At least one
.Fl \-pid
option is required.
Exactly one of
.Fl \-enable
or
.Fl \-disable
must be specified.
.Ss Features
.Bl -tag -width "shader-compiler-metrics"
.It Li per-frame-metrics
Per-frame signpost collection (per-drawable signposting).
Equivalent to setting
.Ev METAL_PERFORMANCE_PER_FRAME_SIGNPOSTS=1
at launch.
.It Li shader-compiler-metrics
Shader compiler statistics signpost collection.
Equivalent to setting
.Ev METAL_PERFORMANCE_SHADER_COMPILER_STATS_SIGNPOSTS=1
at launch.
.It Li hud
Metal performance HUD overlay.
.El
.Ss Options
.Bl -tag -width "-pid PID"
.It Fl \-enable Ar feature
Enable the named feature.
.It Fl \-disable Ar feature
Disable the named feature.
.It Fl \-pid Ar pid
Target the process with the given PID.
May be repeated.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Collect the last 30 minutes of trace data:
.Pp
.Dl metalperftrace collect --last 30m /tmp/traces
.Pp
Print a text overview from a collected trace:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace overview /tmp/traces/trace.atrc"
.Pp
Export a JSON summary:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace overview --json /tmp/traces/trace.atrc"
.Pp
Export JSON with full per-frame timeline:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace overview --json-include-timeline /tmp/traces/trace.atrc"
.Pp
Aggregate metrics by state domain:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace overview --aggregate --domain com.example.App /tmp/traces/trace.atrc"
.Pp
Aggregate for a specific time window:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace overview --aggregate --start 5m --end 10m /tmp/traces/trace.atrc"
.Pp
Stream live stats filtered to one process:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace listen --process MyGame --interval 2"
.Pp
Stream live stats in JSON mode with file logging:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace listen --json --output /tmp/session.json"
.Pp
Enable per-frame metrics in a running process:
.Pp
.Dl "metalperftrace setup --enable per-frame-metrics --pid 1234"
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr trace 1 ,
.Xr xctrace 1
